The paper deals with a problem in dynamic spectrum access, which is a subfield of networked systems and communication (cs.NI). The proposed solution involves the use of an artificial neural network, which falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the management of tradeoffs between different factors, which is a common theme in information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper presents a fully autonomous and distributed scheme, which involves the coordination of multiple agents, making it relevant to the field of control systems (cs.SY).
